column5: Fished Lake Erie for walleye today...they were on fire!  18 walleyes caught.....fished from 6am til noon. Used dipsy divers 75ft back, leadcore 5colors, 30jets 140 ft back, and bottom bouncer.  All with worm harnesses. Big fish for the day was 31 1/2 " with lots of 6,7,and 8 pounders.
nice, got to love Erie for walleye
beauty fish   - where u in the  east end?
nicely done   those flecks of white on the water is what is called a " Walleye Chop " on Erie
Well done !!! Some beauties for sure !!!!! I like the walleye chop out there !!!! My kind of water !!! Cheers
Those are some good size eyes! Nice job
Nice eyes Bud. What part of lake Erie did you fish/launch from? Seems eyes season is here.  Cheers, Ice Fisherman
launched out of the small boat harbor in buffalo 10 minute boat ride and start trolling
Wicked fish Doug!  Erie gold is quality goods man.
Fantastic day on the water Doug !!
Wow! Some really nice size there too! Congrats!
